# Add Flexible Noise Control via New Noise Gate Classes

## Summary

This PR introduces a set of **new noise control abstractions** that allow users to flexibly:

- Scale noise globally
- Tune noise parameters independently (e.g. depolarizing vs decoherence)
- Override device noise with fixed values
- Selectively apply noise on a **per-qubit basis**

These additions improve the **experimental control**, **debugging capability**, and **hardware-aware modeling** of the simulator.

these changes are especially useful for QEC workflows or any work that requires analysis of noise impacts or noise free channels

